node.title: Amtrak temporarily drops its vaccine mandate, avoiding cuts to service.
node.description: The shift in policy means that Amtrak officials no longer anticipate cuts to service next month.

node.title: Teen, 7-Year-Old Among Those Killed When Migrant Boat Capsized in English Channel
node.description: French authorities identified 26 people who died when a migrant boat sank between France and the U.K. last month.

node.title: Man Convicted of Killing Wife with Opioid-Laced Ice Cream to Obtain Insurance Payout
node.description: David Pettis gave his wife 10 times the amount of hydrocodone considered a "therapeutic dose" by crushing it up in her ice cream the night she died in 2018.

node.title: COVID cases in NSW reach three-month high after 1,360 new infections recorded
node.description: Health authorities in NSW confirm 1,360 cases of COVID-19 in the 24 hours to 8:00pm yesterday, as a cluster in Newcastle grows and the Premier delays a press conference on the virus.

node.title: Plexure lays off  55 staff to reduce costs by $8m

node.title: Review: In ‘Flying Over Sunset,’ Getting High With the Stars

node.title: A polite F.D.I.C. meeting is followed by scathing statements.
node.description: A dispute believed by some experts to be part of an effort by Democrats to unseat the chairwoman of the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation board, a Trump appointee, spilled into public view last week.

node.title: A second Omicron case in China raises the prospect of stricter controls.
node.description: Though both Omicron cases were quarantined upon arrival, a small outbreak in a building where one man was quarantining highlights how difficult it may be to control the new variant.

node.title: Four people are arrested in India after a man leaves the country using a fake virus test result.
node.description: The man, a 66-year-old South African pharmaceutical executive, fled his quarantine hotel and was later confirmed to have the Omicron variant.

node.description: Putin also said that Ukraine "is being pumped up with modern weapons, which poses a direct threat to Russia's security."

node.title: Cleveland Meredith Jr. Sentenced to 28 Months for Threat to Shoot Nancy Pelosi in the Head

node.title: Andre Hope, Lone Black Juror in Smollett Case, Questioned Why Actor Put Noose On Again
node.description: "As an African American person, I'm not putting that noose back on at all," said Hope, who was not the only one to question the noose.

node.title: O.J. Simpson 'Completely Free' After Parole Clears 12 Years After Stealing Own Memorabilia
node.description: Simpson's parole, originally scheduled to end in February, reportedly ended early due to good behavior.

node.title: Belarus jails opposition leader's husband for 18 years in 'revenge' verdict
node.description: A Belarusian court hands the opposition leader's husband, Syarhei Tsikhanouski, one of the longest jail terms in the nation's modern history after a court finds him guilty of organising mass unrest and of inciting social hatred.

node.title: Autopsy shows ex-NFL player who shot six people had CTE brain disease
node.description: An autopsy reveals unusually severe brain disease in the frontal lobe of the former NFL player accused of fatally shooting six people in Rock Hill, South Carolina, a condition that has been shown to cause violent mood swings and memory loss.

node.title: The phones aren't ringing off the hook for this travel agent ahead of WA border reopening

node.title: Former State of Origin player charged with sharing child abuse material

node.title: The Omicron variant is beginning to appear nationwide, the C.D.C. says.

node.title: Why You May Never Know if You Had Delta or Omicron Variant Even if You Tested Positive
